Image Pull Secret is used to provide Kubernets CLuster access to the Image Repo e.g. Docker-hub, Nexus or Artifactory.

Command to be xecuted on the Kubernets Master:
" kubectl create secret docker-registry <Name of the Secret> --docker-server=<Name of the Repo> --docker-username=<Repo User> --docker-passwors=<User Password to access Repo> 

In our example we are using Docker-hub Registry as Image Repo;

"kubectl create secret docker-registry <Name of the Secret> --docker-server=hub.docker.com --docker-username=omeshwar --docker-passwors=xxxx
